        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make proper trailer connections.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn on headlights.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that the BROWN taillight wire and the BLACK identification light wire have battery
                voltage levels present.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn off headlights.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the footbrake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that the RED brake wire has battery voltage levels present.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the footbrake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn on the left turn signal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that the YELLOW left turn signal wire is cycling between battery voltage and
                ground.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn off left turn signal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn on the right turn signal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that the LIGHT GREEN right turn signal wire is cycling between battery voltage and
                ground.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn off right turn signal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Activate Trailer Brakes with the trailer brake controller.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that the DARK BLUE Electric Trailer Brake wire has variable voltage levels present
                commensurate with the position of the brake controller lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that Trailer Brakes are functioning correctly by calibrating the electric trailer
                brake controller according to the manufacturer's instructions.
            </para>
        </step1>
